<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A Roman Catholic priest who was caught with 46 pounds of cocaine says he is innocent of drug trafficking and insists he will remain a priest for the rest of his life. Father <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Luis </PERSON> <PERSON> Gil </PERSON> <PERSON> Fernandez </PERSON>, who turned 58 on Wednesday, said he felt `` tranquil'' after a Venezuelan public prosecutor requested a 20 year sentence this week for <PERSON> Gil </PERSON> for trafficking in drugs. The prosecutor, <PERSON> Pablo </PERSON> <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON>, also asked for 15 years in jail for <PERSON> Juan </PERSON> <PERSON> Rojano </PERSON> <PERSON> Martinez </PERSON>, a former priest whom <PERSON> Gil </PERSON> implicated as the man who forced him to deal in drugs. <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON> requested a stiffer sentence for <PERSON> Gil </PERSON> because he allegedly used his status as a minister of God to facilitate the drug dealing. `` I am totally innocent. I am going to wait all this out and I will continue being a priest for the rest of my life,'' <PERSON> Gil </PERSON> said prior to his second hearing before Judge <PERSON> Aura </PERSON> <PERSON> Chaparro </PERSON> of the 40th <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Penal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tribunal </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Caracas </LOCATION>. The silver-haired priest clutched a red-bound Bible in his hand and had a small silver cross pinned to his navy blue knit vest. <PERSON> Gil </PERSON> was arrested last April by Venezuelan intelligence police in Simon Bolivar International Airport outside <LOCATION> Caracas </LOCATION> as he tried to smuggle the cocaine onto a plane bound for <LOCATION> Madrid </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Rojano </PERSON>, who left the priesthood 27 years ago, and his wife <PERSON> Graciela </PERSON> were arrested in their <LOCATION> Caracas </LOCATION> residence hours after <PERSON> Gil </PERSON>. Police found 180 grams of cocaine and cash in the house, <P