<HEAD>CONTRA AID</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> acknowledged disagreeing with his running mate on military aid for the Contra rebels in <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>, but <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> said he and <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> both support the <PERSON> Arias </PERSON> peace plan for <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, including diplomatic pressure on <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>. `` I really think we have to give peace a chance,'' he said. <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> said a <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> administration would cut off aid to the resistance in <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>. He said <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> had also opposed the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military intervention in <LOCATION> Grenada </LOCATION>.
