<HEAD>Store's Concrete Awning Collapses, Killing Nine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A store's concrete awning collapsed Thursday afternoon and crushed nine pedestrians to death on a busy street, civil defense officials said. Three children and their mothers were among the dead and eight other people were injured in the accident in <ORGANIZATION> Porto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alegre </ORGANIZATION>, a city of 1.1 million people 1,030 miles southwest of <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION>, civil defense spokesman <PERSON> Orly </PERSON> <PERSON> Furtado </PERSON> said. The six-foot-wide concrete and steel structure crashed down on shoppers passing a store of the Arapua chain, which sells household goods. Firemen used cranes to lift the broken concrete from the dead and injured, <PERSON> Furtado </PERSON> said in a telephone interview from <ORGANIZATION> Porto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alegre </ORGANIZATION>. He said four of the injured were in serious condition. <PERSON> Furtado </PERSON> said the cause of the accident was not known. `` The building is neither new nor particularly old,'' he said. `` There are no apparent structural changes.''
