<BYLINE>By DAN HORN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A peace group founded in memory of <PERSON> Anwar </PERSON> <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON> marked the seventh anniversary of the Egyptian president's assassination Thursday by calling on <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> to hold direct talks with Palestinians, including the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> The New York-based <ORGANIZATION> Sadat </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION> also urged <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> to permit municipal elections in the occupied <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> for the first time in 12 years. Foundation President <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> George </PERSON> accused right-wing Prime Minister <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> of violating agreements reached by <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s then-Prime Minister <PERSON> Menachem </PERSON> <PERSON> Begin </PERSON> in a 1979 peace treaty. Speaking at a news conference, <PERSON> George </PERSON> cited from a letter signed by both Begin and <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON> providing for withdrawal of Israeli troops from the territories and guaranteed elections of `` a self-governing authority'' there. `` How can you expect another <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> leader to place his trust and to negotiate with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, when <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> under -LRB- <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s -RRB- leadership has violated its guarantees to President <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON>?'' asked <PERSON> George </PERSON>, a former <LOCATION> Canadian </LOCATION> ambassador to <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> from 1977 to 1979. The <ORGANIZATION> Sadat </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION> was founded in 1984 by <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON>'s widow <PERSON> Jihan </PERSON> and American admirers of the Egyptian leader, who was gunned down by Moslem extremists on Oct. 6, 1981. It includes members from <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>, other Arab countries, <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>. On Thursday, the group called on <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> to hold immediate talks without preconditions with <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> representatives, including members of the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>. `` We should accept any delegaton the Palestinians give to us. Both sides should accept any delegaton and if it's the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, so be it,'' said <PERSON> Rustum </PERSON> <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON> <PERSON> Bastuni </PERSON>, an Israeli Arab and former Israeli legislator. <PERSON> George </PERSON> said <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> should convene municipal elections in the occupied territories as soon as possible to permit the emergence of a grassroots Palestinian leadership with whom <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> can talk peace. The occupied territories, where 283 Palestinians have died in a 10-month-old rebellion against <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s 21-year occupation, have not held municipal elections since 1976. An <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> spokesman, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the prospects for Palestinian elections in the territories `` depended on the situation there next year.'' The territories, the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, were taken by <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> in the 1967 <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> war. END -LRB- dh @ ms -RRB-
