<HEAD>London Shares Prices Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices were up at midday Thursday, although they retreated from earlier peaks. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index stood at 1830.5, up 4.2 points, or 0.2 percent, at about 12:30 p.m. local time. The best level of the day came shortly after the start of official trading as the index rocketed 13.1 points higher. Volume totaled 356.1 million shares, compared with 271.8 million shares Wednesday. Market makers were scaling back prices after sharp gains over the past several sessions, dealers said. But selected sectors were still buoyant, including banks, brewers and retailers, the said.
