 later this month of Maximas to dealer showrooms and the yen-dollar exchange rate. `` We also recognize we've got to build up our image,'' he said. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> also said Wednesday: _ <ORGANIZATION> Nissan </ORGANIZATION>'s plant in <LOCATION> Smyrna </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>, has the capacity for another assembly line, but that no decision has been made about whether to expand the plant or, if so, what vehicle would be produced there _ The joint venture between <ORGANIZATION> Nissan </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Avon </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, would produce a larger minivan than the Axxess The Nissan-Ford project is to begin production in 1991 for the 1992 model year. _ The Axxess will have dual rear sliding doors, instead of the conventional right side sliding door on other minivans `` The advantage -LRB- of the Axxess -RRB- is our product will have power, performance and handling,'' <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> said.
