that <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION>'s purchase of the BP shares was, in effect, a rescue operation by a sincere friend of <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>.'' The $ 12 billion BP share sale was a flop with investors because it coincided with the financial market crash last October. <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION> subsequently stepped in as a buyer. <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION> bought 10 percent of <ORGANIZATION> BP </ORGANIZATION> shares last November and gradually increased that to 21.68 percent.
