one of the world's most profitable integrated steelmakers. It is <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>'s second largest steel producer and the fourth biggest in the non-communist world. British Steel had pre-tax profit of $ 708 million in its fiscal 1987-1988 year. The company has shed 80,000 jobs since 1980, leaving it with 53,000 employees.
