<HEAD>Chrysler, Fiat Form Joint Venture In North America</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Fiat </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Auto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> SpA </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> have formed a joint venture to market <ORGANIZATION> Alfa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Romeo </ORGANIZATION> cars in <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> announced Thursday. The still-unnamed joint venture will import <ORGANIZATION> Alfa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Romeo </ORGANIZATION>'s three car lines _ the Spider, <LOCATION> Milano </LOCATION> and 164 _ to <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> during the coming year, <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> Stewart </PERSON> said. The cars will be offered through a limited network of what eventually will be about 250 Chrysler-Plymouth and <PERSON> Alfa </PERSON> <PERSON> Romeo </PERSON> dealerships, she said. The venture `` combines <ORGANIZATION> Fiat </ORGANIZATION>'s recognized manufacturing, production and design expertise with <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION>'s strong marketing and distribution capabilities in the North American market,'' <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Iacocca </PERSON> said. `` We are confident our association with <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> will result in increased market opportunities to help us to reach higher sales volumes in <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>,'' <ORGANIZATION> Fiat </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Giovanni </PERSON> <PERSON> Agnelli </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Fiat </ORGANIZATION> will split the profits from the joint venture, which <PERSON> Stewart </PERSON> said was to be legally executed within 60 days. She would not disclose the amount of money either company is committing to the project. <ORGANIZATION> Fiat </ORGANIZATION> bought <PERSON> Alfa </PERSON> <PERSON> Romeo </PERSON> less than two years ago.
